al system:The biggest buyers of leveraged loans are looking to repeat a str=
ategy that generated gains of more than 60% during the early part of the pa=
ndemic, but raising money for these funds is getting harder.=C2=A0Money man=
agers are quickly buying loans in trading markets and funding their purchas=
es by selling bonds known as collateralized loan obligations. These =E2=80=
=9Cprint-and-sprint=E2=80=9D transactions differ from regular CLOs, where f=
irms buy new loans from companies over months, temporarily funding their pu=
rchases with credit lines from banks until they sell CLOs. =C2=A0Columbia T=
hreadneedle Investments is one of the latest managers to sell print-and-spr=
int CLOs. Carlyle Group Inc. sold another such deal in Europe -- a feat not=
 accomplished there for years. Managers like Blackstone Inc., Investcorp an=
d Ares Management Corp. are also getting the transactions done, as is Apoll=
o Global Management Inc.=C2=A0=E2=80=9CAny savvy manager would want to take=
