ause they viewed this as essentially a regulatory problem.But it has been 1=
4 years since 2008, and the rules kind of are what they are at this point, =
and in fact some rules about bank trading=C2=A0have=C2=A0 been loosened, an=
d so nobody really goes around saying =E2=80=9Cbond market liquidity is bad=
 because of bad rules that must be changed.=E2=80=9D So now if bond market =
liquidity gets worse the story is, you know, =E2=80=9Cbanks do not want to =
